reviews.text: The worst eating experience I have ever had in HK. I stayed at Silka Seaview Hotel with my family. At midnight, I entered into this horrible place. I ordered a bottle of Qindao Beer which costs $30, and SEA FOOD BAOZAI RICE which is $ 50. The peanuts they offered at first would cost you $10 at last. You see, it cost almost $100 HK dollars to have a single meal with beer in this cheating place. You just feel being cheated just because you are new here and didn’t inquiry for the beer and peanuts price at first. To be honest, it is a big shame for this place to make money through such cheating ways. What’s more, it took me about half an hour to wait for the meal and there is no water while you are waiting.
The worse experience I have had . Service is very bad. No water. Food takes a long time.
